## **A robot that caught our eye this week**

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/31e58e1d-3292-49a0-92b1-b80a1f4c6768/image_-_2026-05-09T030257.734.jpg?t=1778292188)
Caption: Photo: Vorwerk

**No more lonely cooking sessions.**

Vorwerk’s Thermomix TM7 isn't fully autonomous, but it's the closest thing to a reliable robot chef on the market. The countertop device blends, steams, bakes, proofs, weighs, and even orders your groceries via Instacart — all from a single touchscreen. However, the prep work and cleanup job will have to be all you (for now).

You can check it out [here](https://www.vorwerk.com/gb/en/c/home/products/thermomix/thermomix-tm7).

———————————————————————————

#### **ROBO REELS**

## **Watch: ‘Project Hail Mary’ fan builds alien Rocky robot that talks and gives fist bumps**

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/586b5dba-cbab-49f6-91ad-2a4308835cec/Group_1000005225__2_.jpg?t=1778292535)
Follow image link: (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FG5cwNxvOp8)
Caption: Photo: Leviathan Engineering

**Fans of the Ryan Gosling-starrer Project Hail Mary are in for a surprise.**

Inspired by the movie, a fan spent months building a tabletop version of the iconic spider-like alien Rocky using 3D-printed parts, a Raspberry Pi 5, and Gemini AI for real-time conversation. The robot has no preset animations; every gesture is generated in context, making interactions feel surprisingly alive. It even delivers the movie’s iconic fist bump on request. You can watch Rocky come alive [here](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FG5cwNxvOp8). 

