#### **SCIENCE SUNDAY**

## **The most interesting scientific and technological breakthroughs this week**

View image: (https://media.beehiiv.com/cdn-cgi/image/fit=scale-down,format=auto,onerror=redirect,quality=80/uploads/asset/file/7855aade-e2e8-4677-8f60-2f15aa0acd37/Group_1000005226.jpg?t=1778384594)
Follow image link: (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gR4Xuslczoo)
Caption: Click here to see NASA’s X-59 jet hit near-Mach speeds in a major breakthrough. Photo: NASA

**1. NASA's quiet supersonic jet hits near-Mach speed in major breakthrough:** The X-59 aircraft hit 0.98 Mach during a recent test flight, marking a [major milestone](https://www.nasa.gov/blogs/quesst/2026/05/08/nasas-x-59-flight-tests-pick-up-speed-with-two-flight-days/) in the race to bring supersonic travel back over populated areas. The jet’s needle-thin nose is engineered to reduce its sonic boom. NASA now plans to fly the jet over real US communities to test public reaction to the quieter sonic ‘thump’, potentially paving the way for commercial supersonic flights over land. Watch the breakthrough unfold [here](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gR4Xuslczoo). 

**2. Scientists claim to have found the "holy grail" gene for limb regrowth: **A cross-species study spanning axolotls, zebrafish, and mice may have cracked one of biology's biggest mysteries. Scientists have [reportedly](https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/05/260508003121.htm) identified SP genes as a shared driver of regeneration, partially restoring bone regrowth in mice using gene therapy. Humans already share some of these regenerative pathways. If researchers can unlock the rest, it could possibly mean growing back lost limbs instead of replacing them with prosthetics.

**3. Astronomers discover atmosphere around a tiny world beyond Pluto:** Scientists claim they’ve [detected](https://apnews.com/article/pluto-atmosphere-kuiper-belt-c6b0ec2e0631f47c25ce18479b14e1ed) an atmosphere around an icy planet in the Kuiper Belt, making it the smallest object ever found to host one. Don’t make your travel plans to the planet just yet, though: its atmosphere is 5M-10M times thinner than Earth's. But if verified, the discovery could mean that small, frigid worlds across the outer solar system may be far more active than we imagined.

**4. Scientists reverse liver aging in stunning new mice study: **Scientists may have found an unexpected weapon against liver cancer. In a mouse study, researchers preserved each young mouse's gut bacteria, then transplanted those samples back into the same animals as they aged. Treated mice showed less inflammation, reduced liver damage, and [exhibited](https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/05/260509210643.htm) zero cases of liver cancer. If the treatment translates to humans, it could potentially open up a new frontier in cancer prevention.

